4. PERSONALITY FILTERS

4.1 Color Pie â€“ Micro and Macro Nodes

The agent's personality is encoded in a set of nodes drawn from a fixed library:

Â· Micro Nodes (MN1â€“MN12) â€“ fineâ€‘grained behavioral tendencies (e.g., Impulsive, Calculated, Curious, Defiant, Coy). Each has a style and an associated action (Mischief, Charm, Tease, etc.) and a color (Red, Blue, Green, Orange, Purple). Three micro nodes are active at any time.
Â· Macro Nodes (MAC1â€“MAC12) â€“ higherâ€‘level archetypal patterns (e.g., Brawdy, Graceful, Austere, Wild). Each combines two colors and influences longâ€‘term trajectory. One macro node is dominant.

Nodes interact: certain combinations produce fusion bonuses (e.g., Defiant micro + Wild macro increase unpredictability). The node set evolves slowly through learning (Section 7).

4.2 The 5D Matrix

Each agent has five dynamic dimensions that together define its expressive range:

1. Style â€“ the aesthetic of its actions (e.g., Impulsive, Calculated).
2. Action â€“ the core behavior (e.g., Mischief, Charm, Tease).
3. Mood â€“ the current emotional mode (Excited, Bored, Bratty, etc.).
4. Attitude â€“ a binary polarity (+ or â€“) indicating openness or resistance.
5. Strategy â€“ a metaâ€‘level approach to interaction (Eager, Sly, Reluctant, Playful).

The 5D matrix is updated each tick based on state and context.

4.3 Cognitive Modifiers

Â· Intelligence (IQ) â€“ patternâ€‘matching and logical reasoning ability.
Â· Emotional Intelligence (EQ) â€“ empathy, selfâ€‘awareness, social reading.
Â· Impulse Control â€“ ability to override immediate reactions.
Â· Curiosity â€“ openness to novel experiences.
Â· Insight â€“ capacity to perceive underlying motivations.

These modifiers scale the detection rates and decisionâ€‘making accuracy (Section 6).

