9. THE CORE DECISION FORMULA

All the above layers converge in a single probabilistic equation that determines the agent's next action:

```
ActionPotential = (
    (Fact Ã— Mood Ã— Disposition Ã— Attitude)          # Immediate context
    + (Memory Ã— CovertWeight)                       # Past influence
    + (Intent Ã— ActiveWeight)                        # Present motivation
    + (ExpectedTrajectory Ã— TrajectoryWeight)        # Future aspiration
) Ã— Personality Ã— (1 - Refusal) Ã— Comprehension Ã— TeacherLearner Ã— Trust Ã— Power
```

Where:

Â· Fact = raw sensory input.
Â· Mood = current emotional multiplier (+/-).
Â· Disposition = personality filter (bored, playful, etc.).
Â· Attitude = shortâ€‘term polarity (+/-).
Â· Memory = weighted sum of shortâ€‘ and longâ€‘term memories.
Â· Intent = conscious goal.
Â· ExpectedTrajectory = desired future state.
Â· Personality = vector of cognitive modifiers (IQ, EQ, impulse control).
Â· Refusal = sovereignty filter (0 = no refusal, 1 = complete exit).
Â· Comprehension = processing lag (0 = immediate, 1 = baffled).
Â· TeacherLearner = influence absorption rate.
Â· Trust = overall trust level.
Â· Power = current power fluidity signature.

The result is a set of probabilities for each possible action. A final RNG roll selects the action, with the possibility of spontaneous "outâ€‘ofâ€‘character" bursts when the imagination pipeline overflows.

