---

1. KARMA / COSMIC DEBT

Not moral judgment â€” just a ledger of imbalance.

Definition

Karma in this engine isn't "good vs. evil." It's a hidden global accumulator that tracks the net imbalance between what an entity gives out and what they receive back. It operates on a delay, like an ecological loop.

System Mechanics

Â· Karma Score (K): Ranges from -100 to +100. Starts at 0.
Â· Accumulation: Every action that affects another entity (micro or macro) nudges K slightly. Positive actions (grace, charity, genuine help) increment; negative actions (harm, manipulation, exploitation) decrement.
Â· Decay: Karma drifts toward zero over time unless reinforced.
Â· Effect:
  Â· High K (>+50): "Blessed" state. RNG rolls for positive events slightly weighted. Others perceive a subtle trustworthiness (small + to AP% or Warmth). May attract unexpected help.
  Â· Low K (<-50): "Stained" state. RNG rolls for complications or misunderstandings weighted. Others may sense unease (small - to AP% or Trust). May trigger suspicion or rivalry.
Â· Global vs. Personal: Karma can be personal (affects only that entity) or a shared pool for a tribe/location (group karma). This creates emergent reputation dynamics.

Integration Example

An entity with high K might, during a moment of need, have a random NPC offer assistance (RNG spike). Low K might cause a micro-expression of distrust in a neutral observer, shifting a social wobble.
